Metrics Dashboard: Train a Logistic Regression model on an imbalanced binary
classification dataset (e.g. Credit Card Fraud or Titanic). Manually compute Precision,
Recall, F1, and Accuracy from the raw confusion matrix using NumPy, then verify with
sklearn's classification_report(). Plot the full Confusion Matrix as a heatmap. Plot the
ROC Curve and shade the AUC area. Plot the Precision - Recall Curve. Then shift the
classification threshold from 0.1 to 0.9 and plot how Precision and Recall change with
the threshold. Print a final summary table of all metrics at the default 0.5 threshold.
